comment: Whiteside (MIA) clamps the arm of Cousins (SAC) and affects his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Whiteside (MIA) makes incidental contact with Cousins (SAC) and does not affect his FOM.
Cousins (SAC) sets the screen on Winslow (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Winslow (SAC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Cousins' (SAC) drive to the basket and makes incidental contact to his arm.
Cousins (SAC) makes incidental contact to Winslow's (MIA) arm on his drive to the basket and does not affect his ability to defend.
Lawson (SAC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Johnson (MIA) and does not affect his SQBR on the catch.
Whiteside (MIA) maintains legal guarding position and does not dislodge Cousins (SAC) in the post.
Gay (SAC) sets the screen on Johnson (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.

Cousins (SAC) initiates contact to Whiteside’s (MIA) arm and holds it through his drive to the basket, affecting Whiteside’s ability to defend. Even though Whiteside makes contact to Cousins’ hip during the drive, the offensive foul is correctly called.
